Enhanced weathering, emulating and accelerating natural weathering processes, was first proposed by Walter Seifritz in 19909. In natural weathering, silicate minerals are transformed into alkalinity-containing carbonate minerals on geologic timescales10–12. The generalized natural weathering reaction is described below in Eq. (1)13:1MeOSiO2+CO2→MeCO3+SiO2+Energy,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
